info.name: gbAPI v11
info.description:
This is a Postman Collection for the [GameBanana](https://gamebanana.com/) API v11 endpoints.

[GitHub](https://github.com/s0nought/gb-api-v11)

## How to install

See [Forking Postman entities](https://learning.postman.com/docs/collaborating-in-postman/using-version-control/forking-entities/)

Ultimate", "_sProfileUrl": "https://gamebanana.com/games/6498", "_sIconUrl": "https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ico/games/5c9d0eb4cf328.png" }, "_aRootCategory": { "_sName": "Modding", "_sProfileUrl": "https://gamebanana.com/questions/cats/613", "_sIconUrl": "" }, "_bIsStuck": false, "_akState": "answered", "_sState": "Answered", "_sInitialVisibility": "show", "_nPostCount": 1, "_bWasFeatured": false, "_bIsOwnedByAccessor": false }, "_aPost": { "_idRow": 10714381, "_tsDateAdded": 1682278652, "_sText": "

as long as your have metadata_mod.json located in the Sma5hMusic folder/Mods/MusicMods/(your mod here)/ backed up, you won't have to manually rewrite the descriptions and stuff. but assuming you don't (since that's not a very well known feature), then you'll have to manually redo every description and gametitle and import everything unfortunately. at least the nus3audio files themselves can be fished and reimported from the modpack.

going forward though, the best prevention means would be to back up specifically metadata_mod.json. as long as you have that file then backport audio from Switch all you'd need to do is reorganize your music playlists

request.description: This endpoint returns a list of submissions, studios and clubs that have gained popularity recently for the specified Game ID.

response.name: 200 Success

query.description:
Which 'page' of results to get.

Allowed values: greater than 1.

Default value: 1

Number of results per page.

Allowed values: 1 through 50.

Default value: 20

How to sort results.

Allowed values: default, new, updated

Default value: default

Enter the search query.
Case insensitive.

Allowed values: string of 3 characters or more.

Comma-separated list of sections to include in the search results.

Allowed values: App, Article, Bug, Blog, Club, Contest, Concept, Event, Game, Idea, Initiative, Jam, Mod, Model, Member, News, Poll, Project, Question, Review, Request, Script, Sound, Spray, Studio, Thread, Tool, Tutorial, Wiki, Wip.

Comma-separated list of sections to exclude from the search results.

Allowed values: App, Article, Bug, Blog, Club, Contest, Concept, Event, Game, Idea, Initiative, Jam, Mod, Model, Member, News, Poll, Project, Question, Review, Request, Script, Sound, Spray, Studio, Thread, Tool, Tutorial, Wiki, Wip.

Comma-separated list of tags to include in the search results.

Allowed values: IDs as requested from Util/Generic/Tags endpoint.

Comma-separated list of tags to exclude from the search results.

Allowed values: IDs as requested from Util/Generic/Tags endpoint.

[ { "_idRow": 22, "_sId": "GameRule.22", "_sCode": "R-CS1.6.22", "_sText": "Under the Warez rule, mods that are built for Xash3D and/or the Android port are not allowed in any shape or form, this also includes taking the in-game screenshots in those builds.", "_sFixInstructions": "

Remove the Xash3D-specific mod files and change the screenshots to be from the original Goldsrc engine game.

", "_tsDateAdded": 1645817452, "_tsDateModified": 1647371921 }, { "_idRow": 23, "_sId": "GameRule.23", "_sCode": "R-CS1.6.23", "_sText": "

Metahook plugins and discussions are also forbidden due to the fact that Metahook requires a specific old build that can only be acquired via piracy/warez. As well as potential virus risk and cheating.

", "_sFixInstructions": "

Remove any discussion and screenshots that showcase metahook. And replace mod files that require Metahook with ones that work with the base game without metahook.

", "_tsDateAdded": 1645817452, "_tsDateModified": 1682270940 }, { "_idRow": 532, "_sId": "GameRule.532", "_sCode": "R-CS1.6.532", "_sText": "

At least 2 different in-game screenshots of your mod are required. This is to showcase how the mod looks in game as well as to prove the mod is functional. Where appropriate, renders made in programs other than the game are allowed to better showcase the mod; These should be in addition to the in-game screenshots, not instead of.

An exception can be made for mods that include an in-game video preview

", "_sFixInstructions": "

Edit the submission to include at least 2 different in-game screenshots. Then request a withhold review.

", "_tsDateAdded": 1682270904, "_tsDateModified": 0 } ]
